quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  4,148,"Allah loves not publicity of evil speech, unless one has been wronged; for Allah is Hearer and Knower"
  4,149,"If you do good openly or in secret, or forgive evil, verily, Allah is Forgiving and Powerful"
  4,150,"Verily, those who disbelieve in Allah and His Messengers and desire to make a distinction between Allah and His messengers, and say, \"We believe in some and disbelieve in others,\" and desire to take a midway course between the two"
  4,151,"These are the disbelievers, and We have prepared for disbelievers shameful woe"
  4,152,"But those who believe in Allah and His messengers, and who do not make a distinction between any one of them, to these Allah will give their wages, for Allah is Forgiving and Merciful"
  4,153,"The people of the Book will ask you to bring down for them a book from heaven; but they asked Moses a greater thing than that, for they said, \"Show us Allah openly;\" but the thunderbolt caught them in their injustice. Then they chose the calf, a"
  4,154,"And We held over them the mountain (Sinai) for their covenant, and said to them, \"Enter you the door prostrate (in humility, worship or adoration);\" and We said to them, \"Transgress not on the Sabbath day\", and We took from them a firm"